BoardGameGeek shows San Juan positioned as the 24th most popular game in the world in all the history of games to date. And from my perspective, with its flaws, this mobile app is FANTASTIC!

Clicking a single card in the hand (if they add the feature) could zoom it. SImple. It also could really benefit from adding the expansion.

Also, it would he great to have the option of the expansion cards, even if at an added cost. So far, however, only the basic deck is available.

I've been hoping there would be a mobile version of Puerto Rico but having San Juan in a mobile version is just as good if not better. The game is nice and light and I love that I can play local games on it.

I would give this app 5 stars if you didn't have to be online.  When I first open the app it starts trying to login.  I got cancel because I don't have data or WiFi on. It goes away for a second then tries to login again.  There is no reason you need to be online when you aren't playing online.  I like the levels and achievements, but save to a cache and upload the data when the person next gets online if you must save it to their Google account.

This is my go to game for unwinding and relaxing. I did watch a few YouTube videos to get the gist of the game a little better having not played the physical version, although this game does have a tutorial.   I absolutely love the classical guitar music in the game. It fits the theme and makes it even more relaxing.

This is a great adaptation of the 1st edition of the base game San Juan. The gameplay is fairly straightforward, but the AIs do not employ different strategies. It would be nice if they did so on a rotating basis.  What I would also like to see is the inclusion of both the 1st and 2nd expansions of San Juan - The New Buildings, and The Events. Perhaps those expansions can be optioned in.   In addition, San Juan is now in it's 2nd edition with updated effects for Guild Hall and Prefecture. There is even a new card now called The Hut. It would be nice if the android app version is updated to reflect all the changes the 2nd edition brings to the table.  Other than these suggestions, I am fairly content with the android app as it runs smoothly on my android phone. This is why I rate it at 4/5 stars instead of 5/5.

Great implementation! Good job. Edit: after quite few plays (solo & pass'n play) I have to say - this is the best boardgame on the Android market hands down!
Did have a bug where the game stopped. Didn't crash, but just wouldn't advance. But so far only once. And I've played about 10 games.
Excellent little board game. I love these kinds of mobile games. Makes me want to buy the physical version.
Love it!  Just like the real card game but no need to find people to play with. :)
Great card game. Fun solo vs AI against others is a bit slow. Pass and play especially   as priority moves between players often and fast.
Better if expansion can be added
Fun game
The game itself is pretty quick and if you like simple games, then you should pick this up. I know the actual card game is a bit different, but this game is still fun.
Love this game, keeps me busy when I'm bored!
The game plays well on my tablet. Large download though.
Great game if you enjoy Puerto Rico and Race for the Galaxy. The app is also well designed and runs smoothly.
Lots of strategy and easy to learn
Great strategy game that mimics the feel of the Puerto Rico board game. Easy and quick to play while allowing for some strategizing.

Fantastic card game port. I'll admit I've never played the physical version, but have played the Puerto Rico board game which employs the same mechanics and themes. This is a great introduction to euro style card and board games. The tutorial is very nice and user-friendly as well.
I love this game. It is very easy to learn but challenging. The game app works cleanly and is very snappy.
More games like this makes my life happier. Thank you developers. Excellent job.
Love it
I have the card game. This is  Excellent for play on your own.
I have really enjoyed this app even though I have never played the tabletop version. Works great on my Galaxy Tab 3.
Innovative complex multiplayer
True to the original, polished, smooth and integrated with Google Play Games. Excellent stuff.
I'd like to play it OTB, because on my phone it's too small)
This is a good adaptation of a great game. Haven't tried anything other than local multiplayer, yet.
Fun game!!
Very good for phone or tablet. Strong A.I. The U.I. is great on tablets and good on phone. Very easy to learn the game, especially because of the tutorial.
Decent implementation, but somehow it is slower than with cards.
Wonderful play, interesting, good AI, and I keep coming back for another game. One of best game geek apps I've played.
I've got this game in cards as well as on my iPod and Android. Great adaptation.

I originally gave this 5 stars but I'm taking away a star because:  1) All the expert AI opponents are male, which is sexist. 2) My achievements have stopped updating. 3) Sometimes the AI opponents get stuck and stop building anything.  This especially seems to happen to Ramiro.
I have a Lenovo 7600 tablet and the cards and some of the text fields are invisible on it making the game unplayable. Please fix.
replyContent: Hello! Thank you for your feedback, could you please give us more information which cards or text fields don't appear or send us screenshots? This would be very useful to try to reproduce your issue. Please contact us on: support@ravensburger-digital.com . We'll be happy to assist you.

content: Plays very close to the original game
Works well. But am having some problems with getting achievements I should have earned.
I am a huge fan of the physical version of this game,  and the designers of this digital version did a spectacular job of rendering the game just as playable and fun as the original.
Lots of fun.  Haven't tried multi-player yet, but I feel like I am getting closer to mastering single player.

Bugs everywhere. Cards disappear, hand won't show, excessive passing to opponent (chapel), and it is constantly trying to connect to Google even when phone is in airplane mode (very annoying). These should have been resolved in testing but I guess the devs needed to get it out. If you're okay with some little nuisances and you like resource gathering, card laying games then you will love this. Unfortunately in its current state I'd say it's worth about 2-3 dollars, not 5.
Great version of a classic game, rate it at 4 stars now that multiplayer works as advertised.

Online gaming limited. Local wins not counting towards achievements. It used to track progress but after the last update, it no longer does. I reduced my rating from 4 to 1. Fix this and I will give those stars back.
replyContent: Hello! Thank you for your feedback. If you have further suggestions or questions please contact us on: support@ravensburger-digital.com . We'll be happy to assist you.

content: I liked the game, my one query is where is the cathedral?
Get the upgraded cards?
This is a fun resource management card game. Great for playing with my 9 year old.
Excellent!
Good game.  Simpler version of Puerto Rico

Great adaptation for mobile devices of the board game Puerto Rico. Game play/programming is almost flawless (just wish there was a way to monitor what commodities are in demand). Really fun and well done app!
San Juan is one of my favourite game. Chasing other player to build your city to make highest score. The game look very well when it's in mobile device.
Multiplayer wasn't working but due to the recent update its now working just fine.
The game is great. I'm just mad that it kept asking me to rate it 5 starts.

This is a very fun, well designed card game. It's based on the board game Puerto Rico, which I have not played, and is similar to Race for the Galaxy, which is also very fun, but not available digitally. Well worth the price. (Paper version is around $20) If you can't figure out how to exit a full screen app, just swipe in from the top or bottom of the screen and your soft buttons will appear.
Really well done game which perfectly plays the first edition of San juan card game. I have had no problems with this app on my Sony Xperia SP. Top strategy game and a good way to kill 15 mins
Have yet to try online.
It's fun
Good implementation of the original game
Fun game with a challenging AI.
App works great. A nice representation of the card game.
Love the card game, and now love this game
I want to play online. Can I get refund since it does not work?
I've only played against the computers but it works well for that.
Would be 5 stars but cannot get multiplayer to work.
Great game and very good graphic implementation. I only played single-mode and the computer AI is pretty challenging. Overall this is a good digital version of the classic board game.
Love the game.

On my HTC one M8 it glitches occassionally. (Instead of prompting for role selection or picking card to build, it just sits there. I have to quit to main menu and continue my game and it will start working again.) Otherwise the gameplay is great. I wish they would add the expansion buildings too.
Great implementation of the original game
lovely reproduction of the card game
An easy to use port of a great little card game. Hope to get the expansions soon.
Well done
It's got very nice graphics, and pretty smooth. Only complaint is that the animations are a little slow, but I'm super impatient and it's not ridiculous. Definitely worth the $1. I'd have paid $5.

The look of the game is great and playing against the AI is challenging but I bought the Android version of this game to play online with with friends.   That just flat does not work. If you want to play the AI by yourself then by all means buy this app. If you want to play with another person do NOT buy this app because you won't be able to.
Great
You've convinced me to buy the physical game!
Very fun, but not a perfect implementation of the rules.
It's San Juan in digital form. Nice music too.
Super fun. Accurate representation of the game.
San Juan is a fantastic game, and this is a beautiful rendition of the game. However, it plays a bit slowly and didn't include the expansion. This is also the pre balanced first edition of the game
Runs well but animations are slow and there's no expansion support. Condado is better for solo play.
Yep
Playing this on my Nexus 5. Great game and tons of fun but I have no idea how to exit. The soft keys disappear when playing. Please create an exit button on the menu page
Such a well-designed app! Amazing implementation of a superior game!

It works great on a mobile device. I'm only playing solo, so cannot comment on multi player. The only problem is that I cannot figure out how to exit the game. I've seen a couple sites say to tap the home button. However, I do not have a home button while playing the game. I have not figured out how to make one appear.
Love it!
Sensible ui for a fundamentally awesome card game
Gameplay is quick and entertaining. Music is good. Graphics are OK but could be a bit better.

This is a highly rated card/board game. I've read about it but never played it. I bought this app to test drive the game. Love it!! Will definitely go get the real game now! Takes a few games to get the hang of it, but worth it! Great game, great app!
Pretty good
I'm happy I can play without friends around.
Could never get the multiplayer function to work. it defeats the purpose of buying this game. I wasted my money.
Yep
This game provides an excellent single player experience of the card game, however multiplayer is broken. It seems the game won't inform your friends when you invite them to a game. Please fix

The graphics are really nice, the game plays smoothly and intuitively. Multiplayer matchmaking is a dog's breakfast though. I hope this Dev and Tom Lehman can get together and make a mobile version of Race for the Galaxy since it's mostly the same game.
I had forgotten how much fun this game was...glad I picked this up!
Takes one game to learn the rules. Takes 20 years to develop strategies. Even playing the AI is awesome.
Simple rules. Tricky combos. Hours of fun
I love San Juan.  My only complaint is that the expansion isn't available.
Implemented very well. Everything about it is excellent. For 6$ tho I could have come with the expansion. AI does not become predictable. Very happy to have this.
Good way to practice and play the game without others. Good practice for Puerto Rico!

worthless unless you want to play by yourself. The local multi-player takes forever because you have to pass the device around multiple times per turn. I bought this because it said that you can play online using Google Play games. You cannot.
The game is fantastic and the app implementation is perfect
This game plays will. No glitches. Well done.
A I is decent.  Could use some more variety
Just like the board game, I can play against pretty good AI without looking for human players
Fun to play and true to the game
Brilliant rendition
Easy to learn.  Fun to play.
A classic game, well made. Works perfectly on my Nexus 7. Would love to have an undo button after I accidentally select the wrong role.
Very good adaptation of the excellent card game.
Good quality
Great game, loads of fun. Easy to learn and master. Watch out for those guild halls!
Well executed. Works flawlessly on Nexus 5 and 7.
Because there are no players. I bought this to play online and no one is ever online. GO ONLINE.

I like this a lot and I totally captures the feeling of playing the regular card game version. Many people (at the time of this writing) have complained that the multiplayer doesn't work. For me the problem is that I don't want multiplayer, yet every time I start the app it wants to connect to Google play games. Please take the hint when I click cancel or provide a setting. Apart from that I have no complaints.
This is an already excellent game; made well for mobile. More like this is needed on Android.
I've played this on my nexus 5 phone and my galaxy 4 tablet. The game runs smooth, and the music is great. I like that I can play solo or with others.
Excellent graphics, sound, music, everything. Love this game and the port to Android is stunningly beautiful.
Easy to learn with lots of ways to win. Multi is broken. Don't buy unless you want to play solo. will up rating when multi works.
This is a really cool implementation of a fun card game

I'm glad to see San Juan finally make its official debut on Android. It is much more polished than Condado. Animations are tad frustratingly slow, but otherwise I have no real complaints. I hope this means that Puerto Rico will be ported over to Android soon.

I'm glad we are finally getting more quality ports. As much as I enjoyed Condado this version just takes the art and gameplay to another level. Animations albeit smooth could use an option to speed up things especially with more than two players. I'm grateful for pass and play so me and my friends can enjoy this on the go! Keep up the great work!
Good, but online play not working for me.

Very slick app with nice visuals. Plays well on my Nexus 7 2013.  My wishlist for improvements: 1) have an option to speed up or disable the animations - it's nice, but slows the game down a tad. 2) On tablets, have the option to display building names on card which have been built. I don't remember all the icons and have to always click on them to see what I have built.
It would be useful to have a better indication on buildings already built (e.g. their names), and to be able to rearrange them.
